1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,839
Elephants are the only land mammals that physically cannot jump.

2
00:00:03,839 --> 00:00:05,679
It's got nothing to do with weight.

3
00:00:05,679 --> 00:00:08,960
Their leg bones are stacked vertically, like columns,

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:12,080
and they lack the tendon and calf muscle configuration

5
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:15,280
that every other land mammal uses to push off the ground.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,280
That design is why they can carry thousands of kilograms

7
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:20,559
without shattering a bone.

8
00:00:21,839 --> 00:00:23,600
The trade-off is zero spring.

9
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:29,120
Hippos, rhinos, even tortoises can technically get all four feet off the ground.

10
00:00:29,679 --> 00:00:30,400
Elephants can't.

11
00:00:31,039 --> 00:00:33,920
Follow for one fact like this every day.

